        "title": "Audit secret-bearing backup files",
        "body": "## Summary\n- extend `secrets audit` to scan sibling backup files for `openclaw.json`, `.env`, `auth-profiles.json`, and generated `models.json`\n- reuse the existing plaintext/residue checks for those historical files so pre-SecretRef backups are visible\n- add coverage for config, auth profile, env, and models backup residues\n\n## Context\nThis addresses a remaining API-key exposure surface discussed in #11829: historical backup files can retain plaintext credentials even after users migrate active config to SecretRefs.\n\n## Test\n- `npx pnpm@11.1.0 vitest run src/secrets/audit.test.ts`\n- `npx pnpm@11.1.0 exec oxfmt --check src/secrets/storage-scan.ts src/secrets/audit.ts src/secrets/audit.test.ts`\n- `npx pnpm@11.1.0 exec oxlint src/secrets/storage-scan.ts src/secrets/audit.ts src/secrets/audit.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`",
